      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Louis Harris (1902-1970) was an American painter known for his nudes, landscapes and portraits.  He studied at the Art Students League of New York and worked in oils and watercolor.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Louis Harris Papers</emph> consists of clippings about Harris and his work, and a few black and white photographs of his paintings.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Clippings are as arranged by the artist, in roughly chronological order.  Photographs are in no particular order.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
